If you couldn't be bothered to read all that just c/p this..
<blockquote>public int chosenNumber;
public int computerNumber;
public int timeSinceLotto;
public int winnings;
public int played;
public int serverOnlineTime;
public int millisecondsToSeconds;

public void lotto() {
if (playerHasItemAmount(995, 100000) == true) { // do they have 100k?
 chosenNumber = misc.random(4);
 computerNumber = misc.random(4);
    if(timeSinceLotto == 0) { // 12 hours...
        played = 1;
        deleteItem(995, getItemSlot(995), 100000);
        sendMessage("Your Number is: "+chosenNumber+", the computers number is: "+computerNumber);
        println("[LOTTO]: "+playerName+"'s number is: "+chosenNumber+", computers number is: "+computerNumber);
        if(chosenNumber == computerNumber) {
            println("[LOTTO]: "+playerName+" won!");
            sendMessage("You win?!");
            if(winnings <= 3) {
                sendMessage("Winnings: 1m");
                addItem(995, 1000000);
            } else {
                sendMessage("It's your lucky day! - Lucky Dip Time!");
                if(misc.random(3) == 3) {
                   addItem(5703, 1);
                   sendMessage("DDS!");
                } else if(misc.random(3) == 2) {
                   addItem(995, 3000000);
                   sendMessage("3 million!");
                } else if(misc.random(3) == 1) {
                   addItem(1375, 1);
                   sendMessage("Dragon Battle Axe!");
                } else if(misc.random(3) == 0) {
                   addItem(2365, 1);
                   sendMessage("Rare gold bar!!");
                }
            }
        } else {
            println("[LOTTO]: "+playerName+" lost! One more bit of winnings will be put onto the next lotto toss.");
            sendMessage("You lost, One more bit of winnings will be put onto the next lotto toss.");
            winnings += 1;
        }
    } else {
       sendMessage("You've already done the lotto in 12 hours!");
} else {
sendMessage("Sowwie! You don't have 100k!");
}
}</blockquote>
Read above for help with the code XD
Now, onto the processing bit..
Search for:
<blockquote>process()</blockquote>
Now after the declaration of the void add:
<blockquote>if(played == 1) {
timeSinceLotto += 1;
}</blockquote>
That adds one to the string to count how long since they've played...
Now add:
<blockquote>if(timeSinceLotto == 86400) {
played = 0;
}</blockquote>
If they haven't played for 12 hours then they can play it again!
Now some code with no if statement:
<blockquote>millisecondsToSeconds += 1;</blockquote>
Now back to the if statement:
<blockquote>if(millisecondsToSeconds == 2) {
serverOnlineTime += 1;
millisecondsToSeconds = 0;
}</blockquote>
You're server is normally configured to 500ms every time it calls the process void so every time it calls it, it adds one to the millisecondsToSeconds string and when the millisecondsToSeconds = 2 then it gets reset and serverOnlineTime gets + 1.
Now add:
<blockquote>if(serverOnlineTime == 6600) { 
PlayerHandler.messageToAll = "Lotto Winnings Getting Resetted in 10mins!";
}</blockquote>
That makes a message to all saying "Lotto Winnings Getting Resetted in 10mins!"
Now for the last and final bit!:
<blockquote>if(serverOnlineTime == 7200) { // 2 Hours
winnings = 0;
PlayerHandler.messageToAll = "Lotto Winnings Resetted!";
serverOnlineTime = 0;
}</blockquote>
That is self explanatory, it just resets the serverOnlineTime and winnings. serverOnlineTime just makes it easyer in life to declare the time. 

